<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920127-0007</DOCNO><DOCID>920127-0007.</DOCID><HL>   Polifly to Increase Provisions</HL><DATE>01/27/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9C</SO><CO>   PFLY</CO><MS>FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED FINANCIAL SERVICES, CREDIT INSTITUTIONS (FIS)SAVINGS AND LOANS, THRIFTS (SAL)</IN><GV>TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)</GV><RE>NEW JERSEY (NJ)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW MILFORD, N.J. -- Polifly Financial Corp. said theOffice of Thrift Supervision ordered an increase of about$4.4 million in the provision for loan and real estate lossesat its Polifly Savings andamp; Loan Association unit.   Polifly said the OTS also ordered it to amend itsregulatory capital plan to account for the new loan-lossreserve and the recent settlement of a lawsuit by a formerdirector. Polifly also said the OTS asked it to enter into asupervisory agreement placing restrictions on growth,investments, and other corporate actions.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>